Title: Years of using this make healthy teeth
Review: I've been using Tom's floss for years and it's a constant favorite. I've tried others, some very new and popular, others the same old "silk" style, and always come back to Tom's. Big reason is that it's highly effective in its job - nothing else compares. I won't go TMI but it's much more efficient and effective at getting out what goes in, and keeping my teeth and gums very healthy. When trying other floss I always notice that my teeth just don't feel as clean and 'stripped' as they are with Tom's. I now buy it by the half dozen because it's just less expensive than single container purchase, and I'll always have enough. Love your teeth? Floss daily (or nightly) with Tom's floss - the old-person teeth you keep will thank you!

Title: Great Deal for the price
Review: I recently purchased the Palmolive Essential Clean Dish Soap Liquid in the Orange Tangerine scent, and I couldn't be happier with my purchase! Here are a few reasons why this product stands out: Great Deal for the Price: The 4-pack offers excellent value for money. Each bottle is generously sized, ensuring that I won't run out of dish soap anytime soon. Given the quality, this pack is a steal! Quality Dish Soap: Palmolive has always been a trusted brand in my household, and this dish soap is no exception. It cuts through grease effortlessly and leaves my dishes sparkling clean every time. A little goes a long way, making it both effective and economical. Smells Good: The Orange Tangerine scent is simply delightful. It leaves a pleasant, fresh aroma in the kitchen without being overpowering. Washing dishes has become a much more enjoyable task thanks to this invigorating scent. Not Toxic: One of the main reasons I choose Palmolive is because it is gentle on the skin and doesn't contain any harsh chemicals. I can wash my dishes without worrying about harmful toxins. It?s great to know that I?m using a product that?s safe for both my family and the environment. Overall, I highly recommend the Palmolive Essential Clean Dish Soap Liquid in Orange Tangerine. It?s a fantastic product that combines quality, value, and a refreshing scent. I'll definitely be repurchasing this again!

Title: Great for adults, too!
Review: I absolutely hate mint flavored toothpaste. It's become a huge problem as I've gotten older. I will say I'm autistic but I think there are more people in the world than will admit it that hate traditional toothpaste flavors. This stuff works exactly as you'd expect toothpaste to work. It isn't dyed, the dragon and unicorn ones are clear gel and the strawberry is white paste that's more like the texture of regular toothpaste. All are smooth and very non-abrasive. The price of the 3 pack on subscribe and save is the best you'll find. They smell fantastic and the blue raspberry especially tastes amazing.

Title: Doesn't last.
Review: I decided to try this product to compare it to Lume as a less costly alternative. Hello brand does not meet the Lume standard. It's kinda slimy--essentially lotion, and the fragrance is OK, but it doesn't last more than a couple hours. I have generally sensitive skin, and Hello didn't irritate me, but I was very disappointed with the performance of this deodorant. And it actually felt like it made me sweat more than I would have if I hadn't applied anything. Don't waste your money.

Title: Great for travel, but so short!
Review: Despite the three star rating I still buy these and use them all the time. We live in Thailand and do quite a bit of traveling to countries where the water is not potable. I use these since we cannot rinse our brushes under the sink water. Definitely not planet friendly, but we were throwing out multiple full-sized brushes that my kiddo kept accidentally rinsing--sooo.... That said, I feel like they could make these handles environmentally friendly and longer. I have to stick my hand in my mouth to get my back teeth and then I kind of drool toothpaste all over the place.
Product 4: Col TB Travel
Product 5: Colgate TB Travel
